      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest (QoI) computed by the model must directly correspond to the clinical and regulatory endpoints relevant to CPB hemolysis assessment.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) derived from the power-law hemolysis model applied to CFD-computed shear stress and exposure time fields. NIH is the standard regulatory metric for CPB pump hemolysis evaluation per FDA guidance and ISO 10993-4, confirming direct relevance to the decision endpoint."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
